      "text": [
        " «عَلاَمَةٌ بَيْنَهُ وَ بَيْنَ أَصْحَابِهِ تَحَوَّلَ اَلْجَدْبُ خِصْباً."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1503 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) was asked about why The Prophet (sw) would turn his cloak around when he prayed for rain (Istisqa').\nImam (as) said: \"It was a sign between him and his companions, indicating that drought had turned into abundance.\""
        ]
      }
